CC  The enzyme modelled by this HMM is responsible for the conversion of crotonyl-CoA to butyryl-CoA.  In serine cycle methylotrophic bacteria this enzyme is involved in the process of acetyl-CoA to glyoxylate [1,2].  In other bacteria the enzyme is used to produce butyrate for incorporation into polyketides such as tylosin from Streptomyces fradiae [3] and coronatine from Pseudomonas syringae [4].
